quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  7,65,"And to Aad, their brother Hud. He said, “O my people! Worship God; you have no god other than Him. Will you not take heed?”"
  7,66,"The elite of his people who disbelieved said, “We see foolishness in you, and we think that you are a liar.”"
  7,67,"He said, “O my people! There is no foolishness in me, but I am a messenger from the Lord of the Worlds"
  7,68,"“I convey to you the messages of my Lord, and I am a trustworthy adviser to you.”"
  7,69,"“Are you surprised that a reminder has come to you from your Lord, through a man from among you, to warn you? Remember how He made you successors after the people of Noah, and increased you greatly in stature. And remember God’s blessings, so that you may prosper.”"
  7,70,"They said, “Did you come to us to make us worship God alone, and abandon what our ancestors used to worship? Then bring us what you threaten us with, if you are truthful.”"
  7,71,"He said, “Condemnation and wrath have befallen you from your Lord. Are you arguing with me over names, which you and your ancestors invented, for which God sent down no authority? Just wait; I am waiting with you.”"
  7,72,"So We saved him and those with him, by mercy from Us, and We cut off the roots of those who rejected Our revelations and were not believers"